    public abstract class AbstractGrouper
extends java.lang.Object
implements Namable, Describable
    Holds the basics of a Grouper without any interface applied so that the extending class can apply the interface it requires
    Author:
    3M Health Information Systems for CMS Home Health

      • AbstractGrouper

        public AbstractGrouper(java.util.Calendar start,
                       java.util.Calendar thru,
                       java.util.Calendar window,
                       java.lang.String versionName)
        Constructor that sets the effective start, thru, and window date to the supplied dates. The start and thru dates can not be null but the window can be.
        Parameters:
        start - - the effective start date
        thru - - the effective thru date, inclusive
        window - - the start of the overlap window. May be null
        versionName - - 5 character string. Can not be null.

      • determineScoreOrder

        public int[][] determineScoreOrder(HomeHealthRecordIF record)
        Returns a non-null double array of int[6][3]. The values in the array elements are as follows:
        • 0 - not scored
        • 1 - score during first round
        • 2 - score during second round
        Stand alone etiology codes are always scored first, then the manifestation/ etiology pair codes are scored second. Codes that are not valid for scoring are not evaluated and there for entry in the array will be 0
        Parameters:
        record -
        Returns:
        Since:
        V3210
